org.jasig.cas.support.openid.web.flow

Class OpenIdSingleSignOnAction

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.springframework.webflow.action.AbstractAction
      • org.jasig.cas.web.flow.AbstractNonInteractiveCredentialsAction
        • org.jasig.cas.support.openid.web.flow.OpenIdSingleSignOnAction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.springframework.beans.factory.InitializingBean, org.springframework.webflow.execution.Action

    @Component(value="openIdSingleSignOnAction")
public final class OpenIdSingleSignOnAction
extends AbstractNonInteractiveCredentialsAction
    Attempts to utilize an existing single sign on session, but only if the Principal of the existing session matches the new Principal. Note that care should be taken when using credentials that are automatically provided and not entered by the user.
    Since:
    3.1
